## 🚀 Getting Started

### 📦 What You Need

```
├── 🟢 Node.js 18 or newer
├── 📦 npm (or bun)
└── 🔀 Git
```

### Step-by-Step Setup

```bash
# 1. Fork the repo on GitHub (click "Fork" top-right)

# 2. Clone YOUR fork
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/orchids-curecoders.git

# 3. Enter the project
cd orchids-curecoders

# 4. Install dependencies
npm install

# 5. (Optional) Create your env file if you wire real providers
cp .env.example .env 2>/dev/null || true

# 6. Start the dev server
npm run dev
```

🎉 Open **http://localhost:3000** and start exploring.

---

## 🐛 Found a Bug? Report It!

| Step | What to Do |
|---|---|
| 1️⃣ | Go to **Issues → New Issue → Bug Report** |
| 2️⃣ | Describe what happened vs. what you expected |
| 3️⃣ | Share browser, OS, and reproduction steps |
| 4️⃣ | Add screenshots or short screen recordings 📸 |

> Include the query you ran, the agent involved, and any console errors.

---

## 💡 Have an Idea? Suggest It!

| Step | What to Do |
|---|---|
| 1️⃣ | Go to **Issues → New Issue → Feature Request** |
| 2️⃣ | Explain the feature and who benefits |
| 3️⃣ | Bonus: link to a real-world pharma workflow it improves 🧬 |

---

## 💻 Writing Code

### The 6-Step Process

```
🍴 Fork  →  🌿 Branch  →  ✏️ Code  →  🧪 Test  →  💾 Commit  →  🔄 PR
```

```bash
# 1. Sync main
git checkout main
git pull origin main

# 2. Create a feature branch
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
# Examples:
#   git checkout -b feature/patent-cliff-heatmap
#   git checkout -b fix/excel-export-encoding
#   git checkout -b docs/agent-architecture-diagram

# 3. Make your changes

# 4. Lint & build locally
npm run lint
npm run build

# 5. Commit (see rules below)
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add patent cliff heatmap to market view"

# 6. Push and open a PR
git push origin feature/your-feature-name
```

---

## 📝 Commit Message Rules

We follow **[Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/)**.

| Prefix | When to Use | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `feat:` | ✨ New feature | `feat: add competitor share-of-voice chart` |
| `fix:` | 🐛 Bug fix | `fix: PDF export drops the second page` |
| `docs:` | 📖 Documentation | `docs: document the 7-agent architecture` |
| `style:` | 🎨 Formatting only | `style: align query suggestion chips` |
| `refactor:` | ♻️ Code cleanup | `refactor: extract agent runner hook` |
| `test:` | 🧪 Adding tests | `test: cover patent expiry filter logic` |
| `chore:` | 🔧 Build / CI | `chore: bump tanstack-start to latest` |

### ✅ Good
```
feat: stream Master Agent results token-by-token
fix: sample PPT slide 3 missing chart legend
docs: add /apis catalog screenshot to README
```

### ❌ Bad
```
update
fix stuff
asdfgh
```

---

## 🎨 Code Style Guide

| Rule | Details |
|---|---|
| 📘 **Language** | TypeScript strict mode — no `any` |
| ⚛️ **Components** | React 19 functional components with hooks |
| 🧭 **Routing** | TanStack Start file-based routes in `src/routes/` |
| 🎨 **Styling** | Tailwind v4 + semantic tokens from `src/styles.css` |
| 📁 **Naming** | PascalCase components, camelCase functions |
| 📦 **Imports** | Use `@/` path aliases |
| 🚫 **Colors** | Never raw `text-white` — use tokens like `text-foreground` |
| 🧩 **Components** | Small, focused, reusable |

### Example: Good Component

```tsx
// ✅ Good — semantic tokens, typed props, clean structure
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card";

interface AgentCardProps {
  name: string;
  status: "idle" | "running" | "done";
  onRun: () => void;
}

export const AgentCard = ({ name, status, onRun }: AgentCardProps) => (
  <Card className="bg-card text-card-foreground">
    <CardHeader>
      <CardTitle>{name}</CardTitle>
    </CardHeader>
    <CardContent className="flex items-center justify-between">
      <span className="text-muted-foreground text-sm capitalize">{status}</span>
      <Button onClick={onRun} disabled={status === "running"}>
        Run agent
      </Button>
    </CardContent>
  </Card>
);
```

