## 🗄️ Mock Data & API Rules

CureCoders ships with **mock pharmaceutical data** for the demo. When adding
or editing mock endpoints:

| Rule | Why |
|---|---|
| ✅ Validate every payload with **Zod** | Catches schema drift early |
| ✅ Keep mock data **clearly labeled** as illustrative | Avoids being mistaken for real evidence |
| ✅ Cite the public source format you mirror (FDA, USPTO, etc.) | Helps future contributors |
| ✅ Keep response shapes **stable** across versions | Avoids breaking agents downstream |
| ❌ Never include real patient data, PII, or confidential pharma info | Legal & ethical |
| ❌ Never claim mock outputs are clinically validated | Misleading users is unsafe |

---

## 🤖 AI Agent & Prompt Rules

| Rule | Why |
|---|---|
| ✅ Each agent has a **single, well-scoped role** | Easier to test and reason about |
| ✅ Prompts stored in **dedicated files**, not inline strings | Easier to review |
| ✅ Always include a **system instruction** that forbids medical advice | Safety |
| ✅ Agents must **cite sources** when emitting facts | Provenance |
| ❌ Don't hardcode model API keys | Use server-side secrets |
| ❌ Don't merge prompts that produce unverifiable claims | Quality bar |

---

## 🔒 Security Rules

> 🛡️ **SECURITY IS A FIRST-CLASS PRIORITY**

| ✅ DO | ❌ DON'T |
|---|---|
| Use environment variables for secrets | Hardcode API keys in source |
| Validate all server-function inputs with Zod | Trust client-supplied data |
| Sandbox file parsing on uploads | Pass user files to shell commands |
| Report vulnerabilities via [SECURITY.md](./SECURITY.md) | Disclose issues publicly first |

🔐 **Found a security issue?** Read [SECURITY.md](./SECURITY.md) for responsible disclosure.

---

## ✅ Pull Request Checklist

Before you submit your PR, make sure:

- [ ] My code follows the project's code style
- [ ] I tested my changes locally (`npm run dev`)
- [ ] Lint passes (`npm run lint`)
- [ ] Build passes (`npm run build`)
- [ ] No API keys, secrets, or real PII are hardcoded
- [ ] New mock data is clearly labeled as illustrative
- [ ] New AI agents include a safety system prompt
- [ ] I updated docs (README / inline comments) when behavior changed
- [ ] Screenshots / GIFs added for UI changes

